         <div type="edition">
            <ab>
               <lb n="1"/>
               <persName key="Σωστράτη">Σωστράτη</persName>
               <name type="patronymic" key="Θυμοκλέους">Θυμοκλέους</name>
               <name type="demotic" key="Πρασιέως">Πρασιέως</name>.</ab>
         </div>
         <div type="translation">
            <p>Sostrate, daugther of Thymokles of Prasiae. </p>
         </div>
         <div type="commentary">
            <p>The stele is characteristic to fourth century Attica. Richter suggested that the artwork belongs to the beginning of the century because
                    “the figures retaining much of the early majesty while the drapery and the
                    developed form of the shrine point to the later date (1927, 258). The
                    composition intimates that the standing woman is Sostrate, the dedicatee. The
                    other represented people are, plausibly, her family members: father, mother, and
                    sister. </p>
         </div>
